==English==

===Etymology===
{{compound|en|pike|staff}}

In the proverb "plain as a pikestaff", the word is a corruption of "pack-staff", the staff used to carry a bundle over the shoulder.<ref>{{Cite book|last=Cresswell|first=Julia|url=https://books.google.de/books?id=J4i3zV4vnBAC&pg=PA329|title=Oxford Dictionary of Word Origins|date=2010-09-09|publisher=OUP Oxford|isbn=978-0-19-954793-7|language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite book|last=Apperson|first=George Latimer|url=https://books.google.de/books?id=7PMZJqSR4sAC&pg=PA460|title=Dictionary of Proverbs|date=2006-05-10|publisher=Wordsworth Editions|year=|isbn=978-1-84022-311-8|location=|pages=460|language=en}}</ref>

